<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE CLINTONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Thank you, Jesse Jackson, for telling it like it is on the Whitewater fuss 
(Column Left, March 17). Most accurate is your assessment of the "get Hillary" 
attitude that pervades this country.We have been appalled at the viciousness 
and hatred we hear from people, even when they tell "Hillary jokes." 
</P>
<P>
 We finally have a First Lady who is using her brains. She is a role model to 
all women who wish to participate in the political process. We consider this a 
continuation of the suffragette movement, when women weren't even considered 
intelligent enough to vote. 
</P>
<P>
 CAROLYN and EUGENE BECKER 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 
</P>
<P>
 * In Jackson's column encouraging the Clintons to "stand tall" amid the 
Whitewater controversy, he sums up the Clintons' lack of business acumen by 
saying, "It's a good thing he went into public service, because he surely 
wasn't cut out for the private sector." What an amusing but alarming 
commentary, and by a fellow Democrat doing his best to defend the Clintons! 
</P>
<P>
 RHONDA WILCOXEN 
</P>
