<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLATFORM; SAY NO TO HATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS E. WELCH, a writer in North Hollywood, comments about the escalation 
of hate in the world today. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When we were children, the cries of "I hate you" were often used 
indiscriminately. With typical childhood hyperbole, we used the strongest words 
at our command to express our dislikes.Children often confuse their anger and 
frustration with hate. 
</P>
<P>
 We have entered an era, like many before, where hate has become accepted 
behavior. Despite the lessons of history, the world is set on flirting with its 
own destruction again. Rhetoric shouted from a long-dismantled German pulpit is 
rejected for the hate it inspired, yet today, from a thousand pulpits, similar 
messages appear. Whether the hate is based on ethnicity, politics or sexual 
orientation, it seeks to reduce the targeted population to no more than germs 
to be purged or poisons to be regurgitated. 
</P>
<P>
 It is only in the throes of hate that weapons of mass destruction will ever be 
used. Yet there is little talk of limiting strategic arms capabilities. What 
good is dismantling the bomb while leaving the fuse intact and armed?  
</P>
<P>
 It is time to establish a "zero tolerance" for hate throughout the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
