<TEXT>
<P>
 Miscellaneous  
</P>
<P>
 Bob Doering, Cal Lutheran's director of athletics, resigned Monday, citing a 
desire to spend more time with his family. 
</P>
<P>
 Doering, 65, in his 14th year as athletic director, will leave his post 
effective May 31. 
</P>
<P>
 "All of us pass through the various stages of life," Doering said. "I am at 
that stage where I desire to cut back on my professional responsibilities in 
order to do more things with my wonderful wife Ann." 
</P>
<P>
 Doering will be on sabbatical for the fall semester and assume a part-time 
teaching assignment until his retirement. Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame High basketball Coach Pete Cassidy resigned last week, citing 
health concerns, Athletic Director Kevin Rooney said Monday.  
</P>
<P>
 Candidates for the position will be interviewed next week, Rooney said, and a 
coach should be hired by May. IRENE GARCIA 
