<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: VATICAN CITY; HOLY WEEK UNDERWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Holy Week, the most important time of the year for the Roman Catholic Church, 
places Pope John Paul II at the center of time-honored rituals climaxing with 
his outdoor Mass in St. Peter's Square on Easter Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 On Thursday, the 73-year-old Pope continues an Eastertide tradition by washing 
the feet of priests in the basilica of St. John Lateran. On Good Friday, he 
hears confessions in St. Peter's. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday night, John Paul presides at a lengthy Easter vigil at St. Peter's. 
After the Easter Mass, transmitted to dozens of countries around the world, the 
pontiff will deliver his annual Urbi et Orbi message -- To the City and the 
World. 
</P>
