<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VAN NUYS; PAROLEE TO 
STAND TRIAL IN STRING OF CHILD RAPES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A parolee charged with raping children in Pacoima and Inglewood was ordered 
Monday to stand trial on 20 felony charges. 
</P>
<P>
 Concluding an often-delayed preliminary hearing that started Dec. 22, San 
Fernando Municipal Judge Roy M. Carstairs ruled that there is a strong 
suspicion that Robert Lee Donaldson terrorized children in a Pacoima 
neighborhood -- the same area where he raped a boy in 1982. 
</P>
<P>
 Donaldson, 34, is charged with rape, sodomy and lewd acts. The Pacoima attacks 
on two girls occurred Sept. 21 and 22 on Van Nuys Boulevard near Borden Avenue. 
Two other girls were assaulted in separate incidents three blocks apart on Oct. 
11 and Oct. 18 in Inglewood, where police said Donaldson was stalking another 
child when he was taken into custody. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Jacquelyn Lacey said the attacks in which Donaldson is 
charged had a striking similarity. The victims were from 9 to 16, and they were 
all walking alone to school. 
</P>
<P>
 After his conviction for raping a 15-year-old boy in May, 1982, Donaldson 
served more than 10 years in prison. He was paroled a year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
