<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: MONTEREY PARK; MOTIVE 
STILL UNKNOWN IN FATAL SHOOTING OF 2 AT CAFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities were still searching for a motive Monday into a shooting that left 
two people dead and two others -- including a teen-age girl -- critically 
wounded at a Monterey Park restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies arrived at the Cafe Mirage, a Chinese restaurant and karaoke bar, 
about 1:40 a.m. Sunday and found Cuong Van Ly, 20, of Monterey Park dead at the 
scene, said Sheriff's Department spokeswoman Diane Hecht. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Namtu Trang, 31, also of Monterey Park, was taken to Monterey Park 
Hospital, where he died of gunshot wounds, Hecht said. 
</P>
<P>
 Vincent Fong, 31, of Monterey Park, and Ahn Lee Dan, 16, of Upland are in 
critical condition at area hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
 Hect said an argument preceded the shootings at the cafe in the Monterey Park 
Mall in the 400 block of South Atlantic Boulevard, an area not known for 
serious crime. 
</P>
<P>
 "Several patrons at the restaurant started arguing, it escalated into a 
fistfight and then one person started brandishing a handgun," Hecht said. "What 
started the fight is unknown." 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested a suspect, but he was released after questioning. No other 
arrests have been made. 
</P>
</TEXT>
