<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH: MISSION VIEJO; POOL CLEANER 
SPILL SNARLS A.M. TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A gallon container of swimming pool cleaner that fell onto Crown Valley 
Parkway Monday morning tied up rush-hour traffic for about two hours, the 
California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Someone discovered the container of muriatic acid about 8:15 a.m., prompting 
officials to close the Crown Valley Parkway on-ramp to northbound Interstate 5, 
CHP Officer Robert Polzin said. Smoke was coming from the container, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 A private hazardous waste team on contract with the California Department of 
Transportation cleaned the spill, and the lanes reopened about 10:15 a.m., 
Polzin said. ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
