<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / CENTRAL: ORANGE; CHAPMAN CONCERT TO AID BOSNIAN WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chapman University is sponsoring a benefit concert April 10, with proceeds 
going to the Bosnian Women's Organization. 
</P>
<P>
 Located in Zagreb, Croatia, the Bosnian Women's Organization provides 
psychological services, elderly care, vocational therapy, medical assistance, 
clothing and shelter to traumatized, raped and wounded war victims. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by the university's Albert Schweitzer Institute, the concert begins 
at 8 p.m. at the Chapman Chapel at the corner of West Maple Avenue and South 
Grand Street in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 "The daily news of violence perpetrated on civilians, especially women and 
children, is shocking and should call people to assist," said Dr. Kurt Bergel, 
co-director of the Schweitzer Institute and organizer of the benefit concert. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chapman Chamber Players, the university's resident chamber ensemble, will 
perform classical pieces from Beethoven and Mozart and other composers. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the concert are $25. People wishing to become sponsors of the 
event can do so by contributing $100, $250, $500 or more. Sponsors will be 
listed in the event program and will receive free tickets. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the event, call (714) 538-6576. 
</P>
