ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH: SOUTH COUNTY; OFFICIALS SEEKING 
LEADS IN ARSON FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELAINE TASSY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fire officials are seeking leads in an arson fire at a day-care center, one of 
two fires Sunday in South County. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire at Kindercare, 25261 Paseo de Alicia, in Laguna Hills, broke out 
about 3 p.m. in a 200-square-foot commercial building. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured, but damage to the outside of the building was estimated at 
$15,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire is being called an arson, and officials are asking anyone with 
possible leads to call (714) 744-0400. 
</P>
<P>
 The second fire happened about 8 p.m. in a house at 31171 Casa Grande Drive in 
San Juan Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the residents were home, no one was injured, and firefighters 
extinguished the fire in about 20 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 The owners had been preparing to sell their home and had amassed some 
cardboard boxes in the garage. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials said a light bulb there caught the boxes on fire, and it spread 
throughout the house, causing more than $110,000 in damage to the structure and 
contents. ELAINE TASSY 
</P>
