<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH: LAGUNA NIGUEL; TRAFFIC AT EL 
TORO 'Y' TO BE FORUM'S TOPIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 How to deal with the traffic problems caused by reconstruction of the El Toro 
"Y" freeway interchange will be discussed at a community forum Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Assembled at the open house will be several county transportation officials 
who are overseeing the 2 1/2-year, $105-million project. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will take place at Design Center South, 23811 Aliso Creek Road, at 
5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County Transportation Authority's goal "is to make the construction 
period as painless as possible for South County residents and businesses," said 
Doug Eberhardt, the agency's project manager. 
</P>
<P>
 "We intend to keep everyone well-informed throughout the construction period." 
</P>
<P>
 A 12-minute video giving an overview of the project will be shown, and 
transportation officials will explain how to use a construction hot line to get 
current information on construction activity. 
</P>
<P>
 OCTA officials will answer questions and offer tips on how to deal with 
freeway traffic during construction. 
</P>
<P>
 Information about express bus and commuter rail schedules will be available. 
</P>
<P>
 The South Orange County Chambers of Commerce is working with the county to 
help ease the pressure the freeway project will place on area businesses. 
</P>
<P>
 "These open houses are a great opportunity for residents, employers and 
merchants to learn how the construction project will affect them," said Kate 
Keena, executive director of the regional chamber. 
</P>
<P>
 "This kind of advance notice will allow people who live, work and shop along 
the corridor time to study alternative transportation options and develop 
marketing strategies." 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the meeting, call the chamber at (714) 837-3000 or 
OCTA at (714) 560-5597. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
