REGIONAL ROUNDUP: PERCEPTRONICS PAYS OFF $4 MILLION IN DEBT, SHARES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Perceptronics Inc., a Woodland Hills maker of computer simulation software 
used for commercial and military training programs, said it has paid off $4 
million of debt and preferred shares convertible into about 2.5 million shares 
of common stock. 
</P>
<P>
 The debt and preferred shares were retired in exchange for about $414,000 and 
259,000 shares of common stock. 
</P>
