<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: IMAGE PARES LONG-TERM DEBT BY $2 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Image Entertainment Inc., a Chatsworth laser disc distributor, said it has 
voluntarily reduced its long-term debt by $2 million as part of its 
debt-reduction plan. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fourth time in Image's fiscal year ending March 31, 1993, that the 
company has pared down its long-term debt. Since restructuring last March, 
Image has reduced its long-term debt by $6.5 million, which has cut its annual 
interest payments by $220,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Image also said it was hoping to refinance its remaining $13.5 million in 
long-term debt at lower interest rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
