VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: VIDEO SHOWS HOW TO BOLT DOWN HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACEY KAPLAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 25-minute video on do-it-yourself seismic strengthening is now available to 
homeowners interested in learning how to bolt a house to its foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Many older homes in Southern California are not bolted down, leaving them 
particularly vulnerable to earthquakes. The video, jointly produced by various 
government agencies, including Los Angeles County, and construction industry 
trade groups and companies, helps homeowners determine whether their houses 
need seismic strengthening and how to do it.  
</P>
<P>
 The video costs $10.50, and may be purchased at local Home Depot stores or by 
calling the International Conference of Building Officials at (310) 692-4226. 
TRACEY KAPLAN 
