<TEXT>
<P>
 Ivax Corp., a Miami company that makes chemical and generic drugs, has 
completed its acquisition of McGaw Inc. in a stock swap valued at about $440 
million, the companies said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 McGaw shareholders will receive $16 worth of Ivax stock for each McGaw share. 
About half a share of Ivax common stock will be exchanged for each of McGaw's 
27.4 million shares. 
</P>
