<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Death in Bophuthatswana -- The caption of two Page A1 photographs in editions 
of March 12 showing members of the Afrikaner Resistance Movement before and 
after they were killed in Bophuthatswana wrongly described one of the men as 
begging for his life. The man was shown with his arms raised in surrender, but 
Times staff writer Bob Drogin, who was present, says the man did not beg. The 
erroneous information was provided along with the photograph by the Reuters 
news agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
